Raw dev notes -- Hebrew News Extractor: Scraping 17 Israeli News Sites (Feb-March 2026)

Built a web scraper/API that extracts article text from Israeli news websites. Started with
a few sites, now supports 17 including Ynet, Haaretz, Israel Hayom, TheMarker, and Channel 14.
Deployed on Google Cloud Run.

The journey:
- Started with newspaper4k but it fails on many Hebrew sites
- Built per-site CSS selector chains with fallback strategies
- Added bot-protection bypass: Outbrain UA for Haaretz/TheMarker premium content
- Cloudflare Turnstile became the biggest headache -- Channel 14 is still limited

Cloudflare battle:
- cloudscraper v3 from GitHub master
- Full browser fingerprint fallback
- Ultimately routed through Cloudflare Worker proxy (browser-side fetch)
- Some sites just can't be scraped from datacenter IPs

Deployed as Cloud Run service with Docker. Cold starts are annoying but acceptable.
Did two full rounds of selector audits -- found and fixed extraction bugs across 8 sites.

Struggle: every site is a special snowflake. DraftJS content models, AMP pages,
paywalled content, different meta tag conventions. Each new site is a mini reverse-engineering project.

Next: Custom domain, more sites, maybe a Chrome extension version.
